This is a refer- ence to v. 661, where Lysiteles says ‘he is sorry Lesbonicus is wanting in proper feeling (parum pudere).' Lesbonicus is here shewing that he is not deficient. Honos nom. sing. is a survival of a declension -οἶς, osis, older than -or, oris. Cf. the adj. honestus, angor and angustus, arbor and arbustum (arbastus adj. ?).
